<DOC><DOCNO> AP880224-0203 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-24-88 0825EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-HongKong-Hostage     02-24 0154</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Hong Kong-Hostage,0156</SECOND><HEAD>Police Rescue Hostages Held 9 Hours</HEAD><DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police stormed a Social Welfare Departmentoffice in a cloud of tear gas Wednesday and rescued eight hostageswho had been held nine hours by a man with a cleaver.   One policeman was slightly injured but the eight hostages wereunharmed. The hostage-taker, identified only as Shum, 44, washospitalized with head injuries.   Reports from the scene said Shum was homeless and had applied tothe office for public assistance. He went there Tuesday afternoonarmed with a cleaver and two knives and demanded to see the personhandling his application, police reported.   When he was told the person was not in, Shum argued with thestaff, who called the police. He locked himself and the employeesinside the office until police broke the door down.   Robert Yiu, a police spokesman, said officers made their assaultat about 1:45 a.m.</TEXT></DOC>